sentence: Drones are often used to take pictures and videos from high up in the sky, making them popular for photography and filmmaking.
Many drones have GPS, which helps them fly automatically to a set location without needing constant control.
Farmers use drones to check on their crops, monitor plant health, and even spray fertilizers or pesticides.
Companies like Amazon and UPS are testing drones to deliver small packages quickly and efficiently
Racing drones are designed to be fast and agile, allowing pilots to compete in high-speed flying competitions.
The military uses drones for surveillance, reconnaissance, and even carrying out missions without putting soldiers at risk.
FPV drones let pilots wear special goggles to see exactly what the drone sees, making flying more immersive.
Scientists use drones to explore dangerous or hard-to-reach places, such as volcanoes, deep forests, and the Arctic.
Different countries have rules about where drones can fly, how high they can go, and whether they need to be registered.
Many hobbyists and engineers enjoy building their own drones, adding cameras, sensors, and special features for unique flying experiences.
Before flying, you need to arm the drone to activate its motors.
When landing, always disarm the drone to stop the propellers safely.
To turn the drone, you can yaw left by rotating it counterclockwise.
If you want the drone to face another direction, use yaw right to rotate it clockwise.
Pushing the throttle stick forward makes the drone move forward smoothly.
Most drones require a 5-second hold on the arm switch to activate.
A drone with 4 propellers is called a quadcopter, which is the most common type.
Some drones can reach speeds of over 100 km/h especially in racing competitions.
Using a controller, you can adjust the yaw angle to fine-tune the drone direction.
GPS drones can move forward to a set waypoint up to 10 kilometers away.
